@@ -1457,6 +1462,102 @@ Exposes the Pino package version. Also available on the logger instance.
 
 * See [`logger.version`](#version)
 
+<a id="pino-context"></a>
+### `pino.context(fields, fn, [...args])`
+
+Runs `fn` inside a new request-scoped context. The key/value pairs in
+`fields` are merged with any parent scope and then automatically included
+in every log line emitted from `fn` (or from async continuations it
+spawns) until it returns.
+
+Nested calls inherit from their parent scope; inner fields override outer
+fields of the same name. Explicit fields passed at log time (e.g. `logger.info({ foo: 1 }, 'msg')`)
+still override context fields.
+
+```js
+const pino = require('pino')
+const logger = pino()
+
+function handleRequest (req) {
+  pino.context({ reqId: req.id, userId: req.user?.id }, () => {
+    // Every log line below includes reqId and userId, even across
+    // awaits or setTimeout, without having to pass a child logger.
+    doWork()
+  })
+}
+
+async function doWork () {
+  await Promise.resolve()
+  logger.info('processing')
+}
+```
+
+Additional arguments supplied to `pino.context` are forwarded to `fn`.
+
+This API requires [`AsyncLocalStorage`][als] and will throw a clear error if it is
+not available in the current runtime. When no context scope is active,
+the normal logging code path is used and has no measurable overhead.
+
+[als]: https://nodejs.org/api/async_context.html#class-asynclocalstorage
+
+<a id="pino-getcontext"></a>
+### `pino.getContext() => Object | undefined`
+
+Returns a shallow copy of the fields bound to the current context scope,
+or `undefined` when called outside of a scope. Mutating the returned
+object does not affect the live scope; use [`pino.setContext()`](#pino-setcontext)
+for that.
+
+<a id="pino-setcontext"></a>
+### `pino.setContext(fields)`
+
+Merges `fields` into the current scope. Useful when a field becomes
+available partway through the scope (e.g. once the user has been
+authenticated). Throws if there is no active scope. Does not affect
+parent scopes.
+
+```js
+pino.context({ reqId: req.id }, async () => {
+  const user = await authenticate(req)
+  pino.setContext({ userId: user.id })
+  // all subsequent log lines in this scope include reqId and userId
+})
+```
+
+<a id="pino-entercontextwith"></a>
+### `pino.enterContextWith(fields)`
+
+Enters a context scope for the remainder of the current synchronous
+execution and persists it through subsequent async work. Mirrors
+[`AsyncLocalStorage.prototype.enterWith`][enterWith] and is intended as an escape
+hatch for integrations that cannot wrap a callback. Prefer
+[`pino.context()`](#pino-context) where possible, because a dangling
+`enterWith` can leak context to unrelated work scheduled on the same
+async resource.
+
+[enterWith]: https://nodejs.org/api/async_context.html#asynclocalstorageenterwithstore
+
+<a id="pino-contextmiddleware"></a>
+### `pino.contextMiddleware([fieldsOrFn]) => middleware`
+
+Returns a connect/Express/Fastify-compatible middleware that opens a
+context scope for the lifetime of the request. `fieldsOrFn` may be a
+static object of fields, or a function that receives `(req, res)` and
+returns an object of fields.
+
+```js
+const express = require('express')
+const pino = require('pino')
+const logger = pino()
+
+const app = express()
+app.use(pino.contextMiddleware(req => ({ reqId: req.id })))
+app.get('/', (req, res) => {
+  logger.info('handling request') // includes reqId automatically
+  res.end()
+})
+```
+
